Activities for Environmental Protection in DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Colorful activities for the environmental protection have been waged in the DPRK as part of the global work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government launches the work for protecting land and environment as a nation-wide campaign in every spring and autumn so as to make people understand the importance of the environmental protection through practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Besides, greater attention is being directed to education, training and enlightenment of the masses for environmental protection. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the universities of the country give basic scientific and technological knowledge on climatic changes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Environmental courses have been set up in some universities and many books on environmental protection have been published. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials in the environmental field are also receiving education on environment and related laws and regulations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Efforts are being made to explain the importance of environmental protection, relations between the global warming and the everyday life, the energy question which is the basic factor causing the global warming and other issues among the popular masses in a regular way. As a result, the popular masses take an active part in the work for solving the problems which have influence on climatic change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the country is taking positive measures for the mass media to inform the people of problems related with climatic change and to give wide publicity of research successes for their solution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Colorful activities for environmental protection are being organized across the country on April 22, the Earth Day. �@�@�@

Papers Observe Anniversary of April North-South Joint Conference
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Leading newspapers today observe the 60th anniversary of the Joint Conference of Representatives of Political Parties and Public Organizations in North and South Korea held in Pyongyang. The conference, held in April Juche 37 (1948) on the initiative of President Kim Il Sung and under his guidance, was a historic meeting for achieving the great national unity under the banner of reunification and patriotism and saving the destiny of the country and the nation, say the papers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the joint conference attended by representatives of 56 political parties and public organizations in the north and the south of Korea the President, on the basis of a scientific analysis of the political situation in the country, set forth it as the most important political task for the Korean nation to foil the plot to hold a "separate election" and set up a "separate government" in south Korea and establish a unified democratic government and thus reunify the country. As a way to carry out it he advanced the policy calling on all Koreans who are concerned about the destiny of the country and the nation to go united irrespective of party affiliation, political grouping and political view. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun in a signed article says that the basic spirit of the joint conference and the vitality of the President's idea of achieving the great national unity and his leadership which aroused all Koreans to the nationwide patriotic struggle for reunification have been fully proved in the practical struggle waged for national reunification for the past 60 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The brilliant tradition of the cause of the great national unity which has made a steady advance since the joint conference has served as a powerful engine propelling the movement for national reunification, the article says, stressing that the spirit of the joint conference and experience gained from it have become a reliable boon to carrying out the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson editorially calls upon all Koreans in the north and the south of Korea and abroad to usher in the new era of independent reunification and peace and prosperity by the concerted efforts of the nation united close around General Secretary Kim Jong Il who has defended the nation and paved the way for reunification with his Songun politics. �@�@�@

Anniversary of April Joint Conference Observed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Progress and other civic and public organizations in south Korea held an event in Seoul on April 18 to mark the 60th anniversary of the Joint Conference of Representatives of Political Parties and Public Organizations in North and South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers there said that it was the desire of the south and the north to jointly hold the event but it could not come true and not a few organizations of south Korea were not able to participate in it due to the attitude of the Lee Myung Bak "government" blocking the development of the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the significance of the joint conference, they stressed that their task in the June 15 era of reunification is for all the political parties and public organizations to adhere to the principle of rejecting outside forces and working for independent reunification and the idea of "By our nation itself" by inheriting the spirit of the April south-north joint conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the fighting spirit and will of the forerunners who went united without any selfishness to meet the common interests of the nation and achieve national reunification are now being steadfastly inherited thanks to the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, they called for paving a new avenue for national unity through the implementation of the declarations. �@�@�@

Solution to "Comfort Women" Issue Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The Council for the Solution of the Issue of the Volunteers Corps and other civic and public organizations in south Korea called a press conference in Seoul on April 13 demanding Lee Myung Bak opt for settling the issue of the "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference said that Lee Myung Bak planned to visit Japan, talking about the "first step toward pragmatic diplomacy".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whenever an opportunity presented itself, Lee fully revealed his dangerous and wrong understanding of history, it said, noting that "pragmatic diplomacy" of such guy is giving rise to the great concern of the victims of the Japanese imperialists' occupation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It held that Lee should urge the Japanese government to take a responsible approach towards settling the "comfort women" issue in order to ensure that the rights of the people are protected and the wounds of the victims healed. �@�@�@

Kim Jong Suk Awarded Mexican Title of Honorary Citizen
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero, was awarded the title of honorary citizen by Puebla State of Mexico on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony of conveying the certificate of honorary citizen was held in Puebla City on April 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the governor of the state and the mayor of the city, personages of various circles, citizens and a delegation of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries on a visit to Mexico, the DPRK ambassador to Mexico and staff members of his embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The governor conveyed the certificate to Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The governor and the mayor said that the feats of Kim Jong Suk would be always remembered by the Korean people and the world progressives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The certificate says that the Puebla State Government and people have the honor to register Kim Jong Suk, a hero of Korea, as the honorary citizen of the Puebla State in high recognition of the undying feats she performed with her noble ideological and moral world and ardent patriotism in liberating Korea, building a new country and carving out the destiny of the great Korean nation. �@�@�@

DPRK's Important Days Observed in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Meetings and opening ceremonies of Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibitions took place in Tajikistan, Belarus and Mexico between April 9 and 20 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the exhibitions were works of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and photos showing their undying feats, books and photos introducing the DPRK and handicrafts representing the resourcefulness and skills of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the functions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mirzoyeva, first secretary of the Gafurov District, Huzand City, Sogd Region, Committee of the Communist Party of Tajikistan, said that Kim Il Sung founded the immortal Juche idea through his outstanding ideological and theoretical activities and successfully built Korean socialism guided by it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 L. Shukolinikov, coordinating secretary of the National Social Federation (for the Union and Union's Communist Party) who is secretary general of the Standing Committee of the Belarus-DPRK National Friend Association Named after Kim Il Sung, said that the President was a great statesman who performed great feats for the country and the people and progressive humankind. The revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered by him has been successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jesus Antonio Carlos Hernandez, general secretary of the C.C., the People's Socialist Party of Mexico, stressed that Kim Il Sung was a great statesman, a great thinker and theoretician and an invincible and iron-willed commander, adding that his idea and feats would be immortal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, film shows took place in Indonesia from April 8 to 14 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun and the 15th anniversary of the election of Kim Jong Il as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the film shows watched Korean films including "The Fatherly Leader among Children", "They Are Together on the Way of the Great Songun Leadership" and "They Were Always Together on the Road to Bring about the People's Well-being".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the film shows the acting chairman and the acting general secretary of the National Guidance Council of the Vanguard Party of Indonesia and other speakers said that thanks to Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il the DPRK has become a country capable of defeating any formidable enemy in the world at one stroke and the Songun politics is a political mode to be followed by the developing countries under the present international situation. �@�@�@

DPRK Guitar Quartet Ensemble Performs in Italy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- A guitar quartet ensemble of the DPRK gave its performance at the Euklide Theatre in Rome on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were personages of political, economic, cultural and art and other circles of Italy, the DPRK ambassador to Italy and staff members of his embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its repertoire included Korean song "Let's Live as We Did Before," an Italian song and Spanish folk song "La Paloma".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK artistes successfully represented all numbers with diverse and individual characteristics, rich voices and unique and perfect ensemble, impressing the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Italian Guitarists Association said that the DPRK artistes completely gripped the hearts of Italians, adding that General Secretary Kim Jong Il is a genius and great master of arts as he made sure that the arts of the DPRK have reached such a high level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary of the Movement for Peace and Socialism of Italy and reputed professors of the Italian Guitarists Association and other figures were unanimous in saying that the ensemble's performance, a good combination of guitar rendition and vocal music,  was something unique and peculiar rare to be found in Europe. The arts have reached a very high level in the DPRK, they added. �@�@�@

Day of Sun Commemorated by Chongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) held events in Tokyo to commemorate the 96th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the functions were Chairman So Man Sul and Chief Vice-Chairman Ho Jong Man of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee, other officials of Chongryon and compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A photo exhibition took place and an art performance was given on April 14 to commemorate the anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Photos impressively showing the undying leadership feats of the President and his noble popular traits were displayed in the venue of the exhibition, divided into four chapters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes presented male vocal solo "Thunder on Jong Il Peak" and "My Country", mixed duet " Warm Is Love of Homeland," jangsaenap solo "Rich Harvest Comes to the Chongsan Plain", mixed chorus "Towards Year 2012" and other numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to it, a lecture was given at the Korean Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched video "Our Leader Who Devoted His Whole Life to Great National Unity".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar lectures simultaneously took place at local organizations of Chongryon. �@�@�@

